Stars: The show will be presented by the Today Show host Matt Lauer (left), while singer Billy Joel (right) a native of Long Island, will also perform during the event

The telecast, 'Hurricane Sandy: Coming 
Together' will benefit the American Red Cross, which has provided support for victims of the hurricane.

The concert, which will also be streamed live on the NBC.com website, is to be hosted by the Today show's Matt Lauer. It will air at 8pm EST in eastern states and be broadcast 'taped-delayed' in the west.

The telethon will be broadcast from NBC's studios in the Rockefeller Center in New York City.

