A spokeswoman for NBC Universal told the New York Times that channels not owned by the company will also be allowed to broadcast the concert.

NBC organised a similar event after Hurricane Katrina in 2005, which was followed a week later by another telethon,'Shelter From the Storm' - broadcast by the major networks and a couple of dozen cable channels.

Financial donations to the American Red Cross will help the organisation to provide shelter, food, and other forms of assistance to those affected by Hurricane Sandy.

